neutron/services/trunk/drivers/openvswit.message:
@Oleg, @Rodolfo, @Lajos,

First of all, thanks for the comment and suggestions :-)

@Oleg, in principle, you are right, the vhu interface might be re-added by Nova / os-vif right after line 242 is executed (i.e. after this green thread has decided to delete the bridge) and we end up with the same problem. That is why I proposed [1], where we ensure the existence of the bridge and add the vhu interface in one ovsdb transaction. The general aim is to leverage the ovsdb transaction isolation to fix this issue.

Now, as for @Rodolfo's suggestion, looking at the trunk unplug code (https://github.com/openstack/neutron/blob/d7953381c45a058d01204aed36e4461764cbe5bc/neutron/services/trunk/drivers/openvswitch/agent/trunk_manager.py#L138-L141) the bridge and port removal are already in one ovsdb transaction. So in combination with [1], we are already water tight, aren't we? What do others think? I just don't want to over engineer the solution

[1] https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/os-vif/+/830103

